%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F23026007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereview%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202012%20linked%20red%2040%20to%20multiple%20cancers.%20FDA%20tests%20conducted%20in%20the%20early%201990s%20concluded%20that%20some%20batches%20of%20Yellow%205%20and%20Yellow%206%20have%20been%20contaminated%20with%20carcinogens%20such%20as%20benzidine.%20The%20agency%20said%20the%20risk%20is%20too%20low%20to%20warrant%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290c67b2e-0a6b-4668-bff6-8f693c0553e8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELess%20evidence%20for%20other%20health%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20ADHD%20and%20cancer%2C%20Makary%20said%20petroleum-based%20food%20dyes%20are%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmade-fun-kids-with-food-allergies-now-mine-has-them-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallergic%20reactions%20in%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20based%20on%20a%20few%20studies%20that%20found%20dyes%20like%20Red%2040%20and%20Yellow%205%20can%20cause%20hives%20in%20some%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMakary%20also%20said%20synthetic%20dyes%20may%20be%20linked%20to%20insulin%2C%20genomic%20disruption%2C%20and%20GI%20issues.%20Evidence%20is%20limited%20to%20tests%20in%20petri%20dishes%20and%20animals%2C%20and%20more%20research%20is%20needed%20in%20humans.%20Here's%20what%20we%20know%20so%20far%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%202013%20study%20found%20Red%2040%20disrupted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglucose-monitors-over-the-counter-track-blood-sugar-health-fitness-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglucose%20metabolism%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20rats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%202012%20study%20found%20Yellow%205%20caused%20DNA%20disruptions%20in%20human%20blood%20cells.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%202022%20study%20found%20Red%2040%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessin