0right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20phones%20are%20ringing%20off%20the%20hook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20the%20call%20to%20resist%20came%20with%20an%20invocation%20of%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVince%20Warren%2C%20executive%20director%20for%20the%20Center%20for%20Constitutional%20Rights%2C%20helps%20defend%20Mahmoud%20Khalil%2C%20the%20Columbia%20University%20graduate%20student%20arrested%20by%20federal%20immigration%20authorities%20for%20his%20role%20in%20pro-Palestine%20demonstrations%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20panelist%20on%20Monday%20night%2C%20he%20drew%20parallels%20between%20the%20US%20and%20authoritarian%20tendencies%20of%20India%20and%20Hungary%2C%20where%20lawyers%20or%20their%20clients%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bdisappeared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20envision%20ourselves%20as%20fighting%20for%20our%20own%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20said%20the%20obstacles%20to%20resisting%20Trump%20were%20significant.%20A%20lawyer%20who%20retired%20after%20a%20career%20in%20banking%20worried%20he%20may%20have%20to%20buy%20his%20own%20legal%20malpractice%20insurance%20policy%20if%20he%20wanted%20to%20volunteer.%20For%20his%20whole%20career%2C%20he%20said%2C%20his%20employers%20had%20always%20dealt%20with%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20raised%20a%20similar%20issue%3A%20He%20no%20longer%20had%20access%20to%20pricey%20legal%20research%20tools%20like%20Westlaw%20or%20Lexis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Pioch%2C%20a%20business%20litigator%20who%20moderated%20one%20of%20the%20panels%2C%20said%20that%20Big%20Law%20firms%20don't%20incentivize%20their%20younger%20lawyers%20to%20be%20civically%20involved.%20Most%20have%20policies%20that%20encourage%20pro%20bono%2C%20but%20the%20focus%20is%20generally%20on%20billable%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20how%20we've%20quantified%20everything%2C%20you%20really%20miss%20out%20on%20participating%20in%20organizations%20like%20the%20bar%20association%20because%20there's%20no%20benefit%20to%20doing%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pioch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Muhammad%20U.%20Faridi%2C%20president%20of%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Bar%20Association%2C%20opens%20Monday%20night's%20%26quot%3BDefending%20Justice%26quot%3B%20program.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68080858c6ad288d147ed8e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMuhammad%20U.%20Faridi%2C%20president%20of%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Bar%20Association%2C%20opens%20Monday%20night's%20%26quot%3BDefending%20Justice%26quot%3B%20program.%3Cp%3ERick%20Kopstein%2FNYC%20Bar%20Association%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c386e3e2-e39b-4803-9405-09d3a67e01f3%5C%22%3EFear%20and%20loathing%20in%20Big%20Law%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evening's%20conversation%20also%20touched%20on%20the%20red-hot%20divide%20between%20those%20Big%20Law%20firms%20that%20have%20cut%20deals%20with%20Trump%20and%20those%20that%20are%20fighting%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Paul%20Weiss%2C%20Milbank%20and%20A%26amp%3BO%20Shearman%20%E2%80%94%20have%20agreed%20to%20collectively%20devote%20%24940%20million%20in%20pro%20bono%20time%20to%20priorities%20that%20dovetail%20with%20Trump's%20interests.%20Meanwhile%2C%20firms%20that%20have%20resisted%20Trump's%20demands%2C%20including%20Jenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%2C%20Covington%20%26amp%3B%20Burling%2C%20and%20WilmerHale%2C%20stand%20head%20and%20shoulders%20above%20other%20firms%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20volunteering%20for%20pro%20bono%20projects%2C%20one%20speaker%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanelist%20Shira%20A.%20Scheindlin%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20district%20court%20judge%2C%20earned%20the%20biggest%20applause%20of%20the%20evening%20by%20wishing%20aloud%20that%20the%20law%20firms%20that%20capitulated%20had%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the